The authors used immobilized non-selective kinase inhibitors (kinobeads) to pull down proteins from cell lysates and the bound proteins were quantified in parallel by mass spectrometry .

Most IPI protein identifiers supplied by the authors were mapped to UniProt accession numbers using the PICR tool (http://www.ebi.ac.uk/Tools/picr/). Proteins which could not be mapped using the above approach were mapped by sequence similarity (cut off 98% sequence similarity over the query sequence). Some proteins could not be mapped using these approaches; these were IPI00012318, IPI00019473, IPI00025644, IPI00052361, IPI00068256, IPI00180434, IPI00183850, IPI00185860, IPI00457307, IPI00640698, IPI00657720, IPI00658151 and IPI00019473. These unmapped proteins appear as unassigned protein entries indicated by an EBI-XXXXXXX identifier.
These entries represent summaries of protein interactions from lysate or whole cells as described by the authors.

The k562 cell line constitutively expressed the gene for ABL1( UniProt accession: A2RQD6 ). The authors used immobilized non-selective kinase inhibitors (kinobeads) to pull down proteins from cell lysates and the bound proteins were identified by western blot. The binding of proteins to kinobeads could be competed out by the addition of specific compounds to K562 cell lysate.

attributeList.attribute: Bantscheff M., Eberhard D., Abraham Y., Bastuck S., Boesche M., Hobson S., Mathieson T., Perrin J., Raida M., Rau C., Reader V., Sweetman G., Bauer A., Bouwmeester T., Hopf C., Kruse U., Neubauer G., Ramsden N., Rick J., Kuster B., Drewes G.
Nat. Biotechnol. (1087-0156)
Bernhard.kuster@cellzome.com

The K562 cell line constitutively expressed the gene encoding BCR-ABL (UniProt accession: A2RQD6). The authors used immobilized non-selective kinase inhibitors (kinobeads) to pull down proteins from cell lysates and the bound proteins were quantified in parallel by mass spectrometry. The binding of proteins to kinobeads could be competed out by the addition of specific compounds to K562 cell lysate. For each compound, three independent quadruplexed experiments (vehicle plus three compound concentrations each) were performed in duplicates, and iTRAQ reporter signal data were combined to display the dose response over nine concentrations.
